\begin_layout Standard
We were interested in finding conserved binding sites by looking for evidence
 of binding sites even where binding sites were not called by MACS.
 We used an algorithm that reanalyzes binding sites using the normalized
 difference score.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Experimental approach
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We identified a set of high confidence peaks in ChIP-seq data using MACS
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Then we used a sliding window to examine the maximum average NormDiff peak
 score overlapping the peaks and the syntenic regions of each ChIP-seq experimen
t 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Based on the background distribution 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\sim Normal(0,1)$
\end_inset

 we used the maximum average NormDiff score of our scanning window to calculate
 the probability of observing a peak as 
\begin_inset Formula $P(z\leq Z)$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Conserved binding sites were identified as samples where NormDiff scores
 were highly different from the background distribution.
 
