\begin_layout Subsection
Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We found 42 new binding sites in HS959 with P<0.05 that were conserved in
 S96 that were not identified by MACS.
 Also 4 of these binding sites were conserved with P<0.01
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We found 76 binding sites in S96 with P<0.05 that were conserved in HS959,
 and 13 of these binding sites were conserved with P<0.01 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
To evaluate the significance of these findings, we evaluated peaks in S96
 using normalized difference scores and identified 98% (885/897) of the
 binding sites that MACS identifies at P<0.05 confidence level, and 60% (563/897)
 binding sites at a P<0.01.
 
\end_layout

